  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6594.59 sitting right between the massive negative gamma at 6590 (-15.2B) and positive gamma wall at 6605 (+16.4B), dealers are currently in buy mode as spot trades above the max negative gamma strike. The BREAKOUT regime with -17.6B total GEX means dealers will aggressively buy any dips toward 6590/6585/6580 and sell rallies into 6605/6600, creating amplified moves in both directions. The gex_surge event combined with 58% 1-min GEX change signals highly unstable conditions where small price moves will trigger outsized dealer hedging flows.\n\nKey inflection points: 6590 downside (heavy dealer buying) and 6605 upside (heavy dealer selling resistance).\n\n**Bottom line:** expect volatile whipsaws between 6590-6605 with amplified moves on any breakout.",
